Start by frying off @sausages{8} (skins removed and broken up) in a #large pan{}. Once browned, add @onion{1} (finely diced). When the onions are soft, add @garlic cloves{2} (finely grated). Cook for a minute, then add @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp}. Cook out for ~{1-2%minutes}, then add @tomato pur√©e{1%tbsp} and @dried tarragon{1%tbsp}. Add @uncooked pasta{300%g}, mix, then add @passata{250%ml} and @chicken stock{1%ltr}. Cook until the stock is absorbed and the pasta is fully cooked. Stir in @single cream{120%ml} and @mozzarella{60%g}. Check for seasoning, garnish with @fresh parsley{}, and serve.
